tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and low globulin and HDL cholesterol levels. Other parameters, including liver enzymes, electrolytes, and glucose, are within normal limits. The findings warrant further evaluation of renal function and cardiovascular risk, especially considering the patient"s age. Clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended.
